You're one of the sureliest people I have ever met in EQ.  How quick you forget what most mages were asking for.  You're easily blinded and easily sway.  Your opinions change rapidly, but usually go back to a negative stance invariably.<br>
<br>
Were you not the one boasting how powerful epic was again again?  How it was tanking mobs in UP and even the big Zelniak?  Were you not one of the advocates that the new pets not have a distinct advantage over Epic given the time sink the epic is?  Were you not the one that also has said, like the rest of us, that current pets (pre-PoP) don't hit boss mobs well and that their procs don't even land?<br>
<br>
The new pets do everything that most mages ask for.  They don't totally usurp the power of Epic pet.  They have Epic pet damage against exp mobs which is more than adequate.  They are a nice boost for non-epic mages so there is a boon there.  However, being level 60 makes them way more raid friendly, which was the big sticking point for all mages.<br>
<br>
GV pets do fine damage to exp mobs, especially epic pet.  Almost no mage was asking for a boost there.  What we were asking for is a boost against boss mob encounters and we got that with the new pets.<br>
<br>
Mages in PoP rule.  I was in PoD today with another epic mage.  Everyone in our party died except the two of us with two underbulks still alive.  We killed them both and then CoH'ed the people back to our exp so we could keep going.  We have plenty of power and with more AA I'll have even more.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure what you're looking for but with new pets I think we are nicely balanced for the first time since I've been playing.  Love playing my mage now.<br>
